Crokerstrete is Grokerton, the eastern suburb of Cardiff. Bawdrip or Baggedrippe came from Somerset, where they held the Manor and from it derived their name. Cogan was also a Somerset name, and they held Stretcholt and Huntspill. Sir Milo de (logan was one of the conquerors and settlers in the south of Irelnnd. The family also gave its name to a Manor and Parish west of Oai-diff.
